HEADWORD: Untemper
<hw>Un*tem"per</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>temper</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of temper, or
of the proper degree of temper; to make soft.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untemperate</ent>⟦br⟧
